    // This contributes a factor of 2 to the final answer.

    // --- Analysis of people to the left (i < pos) ---
    // An person i < pos is visible if and only if they choose 'L'.
    // We need exactly 'k_L' people from the left to choose 'L', where 0 <= k_L <= leftCount.
    // The number of ways to choose exactly k_L people from 'leftCount' is C(leftCount, k_L).

    // --- Analysis of people to the right (i > pos) ---
    // An person i > pos is visible if and only if they choose 'R'.
    // We need exactly 'k_R' people from the right to choose 'R', where 0 <= k_R <= rightCount.
    // The number of ways to choose exactly k_R people from 'rightCount' is C(rightCount, k_R).

